snippet.title: Building Images For The Secure Supply Chain in 1 Minute ‚Ä¢ Adrian Mouat ‚Ä¢ GOTO 2023
snippet.description:
This presentation was recorded at GOTO Amsterdam 2023. #GOTOcon #GOTOams
https://gotoams.nl

Adrian Mouat - Author of 'Using Docker' & Dev Rel at Chainguard @AdrianMouat 

Check out the full talk:
https://youtu.be/bZTlLAg9UZ4

RESOURCES
https://github.com/wolfi-dev/advisories
https://github.com/chainguard-images/images

Adrian
https://twitter.com/adrianmouat
https://github.com/amouat
https://linkedin.com/in/adrianmouat
http://www.adrianmouat.com

ABSTRACT
Security scans getting you down? Is the security team complaining about the CVE count in your images? Want to improve your SLSA level but don't know where to start?
You're not alone - all organisations face these issues. This talk will walk through techniques and tooling that you can use today to address these concerns.

In particular it will cover:
‚Ä¢ how to reduce the CVE count in your images by minimising dependencies
‚Ä¢ the importance of updating images and dependencies
‚Ä¢ using apko to build container images with SBOMs and complete reproducibility [...]

Download slides and read the full abstract here:
https://gotoams.nl/2023/sessions/2472

snippet.title: Demo of Azure AI & pgvector with Azure Database for PostgreSQL
snippet.description:
Demo of Azure AI being used with Azure Database for PostgreSQL and pgvector. Based on a demo given by Claire Giordano on the keynote stage at PASS Data Community Summit, this video showcases how you can improve the relevance of search results on a recipe website by using Azure OpenAI. Specifically the demo shows how you can use the new azure_ai (Preview) extension along with the open source pgvector extension and the Azure Database for PostgreSQL managed service to deliver semantic search results‚Äîas compared to search results you could obtain in the past via pattern matching with the LIKE clause in Postgres, or via Postgres full text search.

The demo also shows how azure_ai gives you an integration between Azure Database for PostgreSQL and the Azure AI Language service, so you can do things like sentiment analysis, language detection, and PII redaction. 

In combination with the Azure Database for PostgreSQL service and pgvector, the new azure_ai extension to Postgres gives you the capability to build entirely new classes of applications‚Äîentirely in Postgres.

‚ñ∫ Video bookmarks:
‚è©  00:00 Introduction of demo
‚è©  00:25 How things worked before with LIKE
‚è©  01:09 What about full text search?
‚è©  01:45 New azure_ai extension to Postgres
‚è©  03:52 Sentiment analysis & Azure AI Language service
‚è©  04:28 Language detection
‚è©  04:47 PII redaction
‚è©  05:15 Conclusion: azure_ai & pgvector with PostgreSQL 

‚úÖ Blog post: Introducing the azure_ai extension to Azure Database for PostgreSQL: https://aka.ms/blog-azure-ai

snippet.title: PaulyBrowserous - Sudo for Windows, new FTC complaint, Mozilla refocuses
snippet.description:
On this spicy episode of Windows Weekly, Paul, Leo, and Richard try to pronounce "Sudo," watch an expensive Copilot ad, marvel at big Arm revenues, discuss the latest in internet browser news, and debate the FTC's motivations as they go after Microsoft once again!

Windows 11
‚Ä¢ Big changes in Insider, with Canary and Dev moving to the same 24H2 builds
‚Ä¢ Windows 11 is going to get its AI moment this year
‚Ä¢ With the announcement of 24H2, does that mean nothing big mid-year as rumors suggested?
‚Ä¢ Patch Tuesday arrives. Copilot moves to the right of the system tray after 10 seconds of testing
‚Ä¢ Brave ships its browser on Arm in stable
‚Ä¢ Windows will likely get an AI game upscaling feature

AI/Antitrust
‚Ä¢ Report: Azure is allegedly 2/3rds the size of AWS by revenue, thanks to AI
‚Ä¢ Microsoft Bing and Edge avoid the EU DMA
‚Ä¢ Google Gemini officially replaces Bard
‚Ä¢ Grammarly lays off 230 to focus on AI
‚Ä¢ Mozilla scales back dramatically, will focus on AI in Firefox
‚Ä¢ Arc Sync comes to Arc on Mac only

Cloud/server/dev
‚Ä¢ Google One surpasses 100 million users. New AI tier is coming to take on Copilot Pro
‚Ä¢ Arm revenues are in. Look at those margins!
‚Ä¢ Notion acquires Skiff. Ladies and gentlemen, the Notion Office is coming
‚Ä¢ .NET 9 Preview 1 arrives. Are annual updates too much?

Xbox
‚Ä¢ Xbox says it will come clean on its strategy
‚Ä¢ The FTC claims that Xbox layoffs violate the terms of its Activision Blizzard acquisition promises
‚Ä¢ Microsoft tells the court that the FTC is wrong on multiple levels
‚Ä¢ There‚Äôs a new Xbox system update
‚Ä¢ Sony doesn‚Äôt meet its quarterly PS5 sales target, will miss its annual target, and the PS5 is falling off a cliff
‚Ä¢ Disney invests $1.5 billion in Epic Games. ‚ÄúF U, Apple!‚Äù
‚Ä¢ Flight Simulator jumps the Minecraft Shark

Tips and Picks
‚Ä¢ Tip of the Week: Microsoft PC Manager - Avoid at all costs
‚Ä¢ App Picks of the Week: DuckDuckGo browser, Apple TV+, Apple Music, Apple Devices for Windows
‚Ä¢ RunAs Radio this week: Maximizing Metadata with Emily Manicini
‚Ä¢ Brown liquor pick of the week: Starward Pedro Ximenez Cask

Hosts: Leo Laporte, Paul Thurrott, and Richard Campbell

localized.title: PaulyBrowserous - Sudo for Windows, new FTC complaint, Mozilla refocuses
localized.description:
On this spicy episode of Windows Weekly, Paul, Leo, and Richard try to pronounce "Sudo," watch an expensive Copilot ad, marvel at big Arm revenues, discuss the latest in internet browser news, and debate the FTC's motivations as they go after Microsoft once again!

Windows 11
‚Ä¢ Big changes in Insider, with Canary and Dev moving to the same 24H2 builds
‚Ä¢ Windows 11 is going to get its AI moment this year
‚Ä¢ With the announcement of 24H2, does that mean nothing big mid-year as rumors suggested?
‚Ä¢ Patch Tuesday arrives. Copilot moves to the right of the system tray after 10 seconds of testing
‚Ä¢ Brave ships its browser on Arm in stable
‚Ä¢ Windows will likely get an AI game upscaling feature

‚Ä¢ Brown liquor pick of the week: Starward Pedro Ximenez Cask
